# NOHS Website - Multi-Page Structure

Your website has been reorganized into separate HTML files for each section!

## File Structure

```
nohs-website/
│
├── index.html          (Home page with carousel)
├── about.html          (About section)
├── developers.html     (Developers section)
├── achievements.html   (Achievements section)
├── location.html       (Location section)
├── contact.html        (Contact form section)
│
├── css/
│   └── style.css       (All your styles)
│
├── js/
│   ├── carousel.js     (Home page carousel functionality)
│   └── contact.js      (Contact form functionality)
│
└── images/             (Your existing images folder)
    ├── logonohs.png
    ├── rizal.png
    ├── mainbg.png
    ├── prinsi.jpg
    ├── rizal2.png
    ├── titsir.jpg
    ├── titsir2.jpg
    ├── tecee.jpg
    ├── tisi.jpg
    ├── mapnohs.png
    ├── youtube.png
    └── facebook.png
```

## What Changed?

✅ **Separate HTML files** - Each section now has its own page
✅ **Working navigation** - Click any nav link to go to that page
✅ **Active state** - Current page is highlighted in the navigation
✅ **Shared styles** - All pages use the same CSS file
✅ **Organized JavaScript** - Carousel code only loads on home page, contact form only on contact page
✅ **Same design** - Everything looks and works exactly like before!

## How to Use

1. Copy your existing `images/` folder into the `nohs-website/` directory
2. Open `index.html` in your browser
3. Navigate between pages using the menu

All functionality is preserved - the carousel still works on the home page, and the contact form still works on the contact page!
